overview: The user initiated a request to fix a pull request with numerous
  issues, including critical security flaws, functional bugs, and failing Vercel
  deployments. The agent systematically addressed these, starting with lint
  errors and insecure authentication, which was upgraded to HMAC-signed sessions
  and adapted for Vercel's Edge Runtime. API routes received pagination, and PDF
  generation bugs (NaN values, minute calculations, hardcoded user) were
  resolved. Form fields were improved to handle nulls, and time inputs gained
  regex validation. The Vercel deployment proved challenging, first due to a
  missing Prisma database URL, then a critical Next.js security vulnerability.
  Updating Next.js led to further breaking changes in Prisma 7 (requiring schema
  adjustments) and the removal of the  command, which necessitated
  updating ESLint scripts. The agent successfully navigated these complexities,
  ensuring all identified issues were resolved and the application was buildable
  and deployable.
